---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { products } from '../../data/products';
import type { Product } from '../../data/products';

const slugOrder = ['august-wifi-smart-lock-4th-gen', 'level-lock-touch', 'yale-assure-lock-2', 'ultraloq-u-bolt-pro-wifi'];
const picks = slugOrder.map(slug => products.find(p => p.slug === slug)!).filter(Boolean) as Product[];
const topPick = picks[0];
---

<Layout
  title="Best Smart Locks for Renters (2026): No Landlord Permission Needed"
  description="The best smart locks for renters — options that won't violate your lease. Our top pick attaches to your existing deadbolt and leaves no exterior trace."
>
  <div class="bg-amber-50 border-b border-amber-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-2 text-xs text-amber-800 text-center">
      This site earns commissions from purchases made through our links at no extra cost to you.
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <nav class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-green-700">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <a href="/smart-home" class="hover:text-green-700">Smart Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      Best Smart Locks for Renters
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 leading-tight">
      Best Smart Locks for Renters (2026): No Landlord Permission Needed
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 · 4 products compared</p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Most smart locks replace your existing deadbolt entirely — which is usually fine for homeowners
      but can be a lease violation or flat-out prohibited if you're renting. The options below are
      specifically selected for rental situations: they either install without replacing the deadbolt
      (so the exterior looks unchanged), or they're easy to swap back when you move out.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      What to look for as a renter: interior-only installation (no exterior changes), reversibility,
      and minimal drilling. Our top pick checks all three boxes and installs in under 10 minutes.
    </p>

    <!-- Renter checklist callout -->
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-100 rounded-2xl p-5 mb-10">
      <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-sm">Before you buy: 3 questions to ask as a renter</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">1.</span>Does my lease prohibit lock replacement? (Check before buying any full deadbolt replacement.)</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">2.</span>Does the exterior appearance change? (Landlords or HOAs may object even if the lease doesn't explicitly prohibit it.)</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">3.</span>Can I take it with me when I move? (Interior-only locks move with you; full deadbolt replacements don't without reinstalling the original.)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Top Pick Box -->
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Our Top Pick for Renters</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{topPick.name}</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-2">{topPick.tagline}</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700">${topPick.price}</p>
        </div>
        <a
          href={topPick.affiliateUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="nofollow noopener"
          class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap text-center"
        >
          Check Price on Amazon →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Comparison Table -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Quick Comparison</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-12 rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Product</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Price</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Installation</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Ecosystems</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Entry Methods</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {picks.map((p, i) => (
            <tr class={`border-b border-gray-100 ${i === 0 ? 'bg-green-50' : 'hover:bg-gray-50'}`}>
              <td class="p-3">
                <a href={`#${p.slug}`} class="font-medium text-gray-900 hover:text-green-700">{p.name}</a>
                {i === 0 && <span class="ml-2 text-xs bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full font-medium">Top Pick</span>}
              </td>
              <td class="p-3 font-medium">${p.price}</td>
              <td class="p-3">{p.specs['Installation']}</td>
              <td class="p-3">{p.specs['Smart Platforms']}</td>
              <td class="p-3">{p.specs['Entry Methods'] ?? 'App + key'}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Individual Reviews -->
    {picks.map((product, i) => (
      <section id={product.slug} class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
        <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">
            {i === 0 ? '🏆 Best for Renters' : i === 1 ? '🥈 Best Invisible Option' : i === 2 ? '🥉 Best Build Quality' : '💰 Best Value'}
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{product.name}</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">${product.price} &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {product.rating}/5</p>
            </div>
            <a
              href={product.affiliateUrl}
              target="_blank"
              rel="nofollow noopener"
              class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap"
            >
              Check on Amazon →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">{product.tagline}</p>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-4 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Key Specs</p>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8">
            {Object.entries(product.specs).map(([key, val]) => (
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5 border-b border-gray-100 last:border-0">
                <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">{key}</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">{val}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-sm">Pros</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {product.pros.map(pro => (
                <li class="text-sm text-gray-700 flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span>
                  {pro}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-sm">Cons</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {product.cons.map(con => (
                <li class="text-sm text-gray-700 flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✗</span>
                  {con}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <a
          href={product.affiliateUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="nofollow noopener"
          class="inline-block border border-green-700 text-green-700 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-700 hover:text-white transition-colors"
        >
          Buy {product.name} on Amazon →
        </a>
      </section>
    ))}

    <!-- Buying Guide -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Smart Lock Buying Guide for Renters</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Interior-only vs full deadbolt replacement</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Interior-only locks (August, Level) attach to the interior side of your existing deadbolt and don't change the exterior appearance at all. Full deadbolt replacements (Ultraloq, Yale) swap out the entire lock mechanism. The advantage of full replacements: more features, keypad on the exterior, and no dependency on your existing deadbolt being compatible. The disadvantage: requires more work to revert when you move out, and may require landlord permission.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What to say to your landlord</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">If you need landlord permission for a full deadbolt replacement: frame it as a security upgrade, offer to provide them with a key or door code, and emphasize that you'll restore the original lock when you leave. Most landlords who aren't explicitly hostile to modifications will approve a Ultraloq or Yale swap under these terms.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can you take your smart lock to your next apartment?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">August and Level Lock are fully portable — uninstall them and bring them to your next place. Full deadbolt replacements (Ultraloq, Yale) can also move with you, but you need to reinstall the original deadbolt when you move out — keep it in a drawer. The August is specifically designed to be the take-it-with-you renter option.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Smart lock security: are they safe?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Major brands (August, Yale, Level) use AES-128 or AES-256 encryption and are significantly harder to defeat than a physical lock pick. The main vulnerability is your phone or account being compromised — use two-factor authentication and don't share login credentials. The physical deadbolt remains your primary security layer; the smart component adds convenience and access logging on top.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Will the August Smart Lock work with my existing deadbolt?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The August 4th Gen works with most standard single-cylinder deadbolts, including most Schlage, Kwikset, Yale, and similar brands. It does not work with double-cylinder deadbolts (which require a key on both sides), chain locks, or European-style mortise locks. August's compatibility page has a full list — check before buying if your deadbolt is unusual.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Does the Level Lock Touch require an iPhone?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">It requires Apple HomeKit and an Apple Home Hub (Apple TV 4K or HomePod) for remote access and auto-unlock. At the door, you can also use the capacitive touch ring on the lock itself to lock/unlock with a tap pattern — this works without any phone. For Android users or non-Apple households, the Level Lock is not the right choice.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What happens if my smart lock battery dies?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">All four locks in this guide use standard AA or similar batteries and will warn you via the app when batteries are low — typically weeks before they die. In a dead battery situation, most locks still have a physical key backup. The August has a 9-volt emergency power contact on the exterior keypad (if you have one purchased separately). Keep a spare key with a trusted person regardless.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I give my dog walker or cleaner temporary access?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes — this is one of the main reasons renters buy smart locks. August, Yale, and Ultraloq all let you create time-limited access codes or virtual keys that expire automatically. You can give someone access for a specific window (Tuesday 10am–2pm) and revoke it instantly from your phone. No need to cut and retrieve physical keys.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Guides -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Related Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/smart-home/best-smart-thermostat-no-c-wire" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Smart Home</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Smart Thermostats Without C-Wire →</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/backup-power/best-portable-power-station-under-500" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Backup Power</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Portable Power Stations Under $500 →</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>
